.TH "rdma_rw_mr_factor" 9 "rdma_rw_mr_factor" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rdma_rw_mr_factor \- return number of MRs required for a payload
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" rdma_rw_mr_factor
.BI "(struct ib_device *device "  ","
.BI "u8 port_num "  ","
.BI "unsigned int maxpages "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
device handling the connection
.IP "port_num" 12
port num to which the connection is bound
.IP "maxpages" 12
maximum payload pages per rdma_rw_ctx
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the number of MRs the device requires to move \fImaxpayload\fP
bytes. The returned value is used during transport creation to
compute max_rdma_ctxts and the size of the transport's Send and
Send Completion Queues.
